  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "SP",
    "text": "This is a family group photo. It was taken about 18 months ago. Unfortunately, as I've said over and over again, my wife is no more. There's all the four children, my wife, and myself, and the baby. It was taken in Kent. And my daughter, she's got a cottage which is 400 years old, a great big open fire. And we love going down there. And it's-- as you can see, we had a really good time. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This photo, unfortunately, was taken at the hospice, where my wife was very ill. As you can see, there's Frankie [? Rogan ?], and his wife, Stella. And we had a good laugh even there. We were talking about family matters and all that. And we finished up saying, like, if you've got a grandson-- if you've got a granddaughter of 21 months, I've got a grandson of 24, maybe we can become [NON-ENGLISH]. That's his saying, not mine.",
