  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "SP",
    "text": "Yes. It took me quite a-- a while to get this birth certificate of mine. I never knew my exact date for many years. I was going as 20-10-29. And it wasn't until I got this birth certificate only about 10 years ago which I realized that my real birthday is on the 26th of September, 1928. Probably if I had known my real birthday, I probably wouldn't have been able to come to this country, because they only allowed children under 16. And I'm very proud of it, as I've said. And here we are. Cheers. That's-- that's all I can say about that. It's a lot of the boys can't-- haven't got that. They haven't got-- they can't have it, because it-- it was burned down, or whatever.",
